# Implement FullBoundedGrid

The goal is to add a new type of grid (FullBoundedGrid) to the GridWorld project. This implementation will use a 2D array (`Object[][]`) for storage and will be located in a separate project directory.

## Proposed Changes

### [FullGrid Project]

#### [NEW] [FullBoundedGrid.java](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/School/10th-grade/APCSA/GridWorld/src/GridWorldCode/projects/fullGrid/FullBoundedGrid.java)
Implement a bounded grid that uses a 2D array to store occupants. No comments will be included.

#### [NEW] [FullGridRunner.java](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/School/10th-grade/APCSA/GridWorld/src/GridWorldCode/projects/fullGrid/FullGridRunner.java)
A runner class to demonstrate the `FullBoundedGrid` by filling it with actors.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. Compile the new files using `javac`.
2. Run `FullGridRunner` to ensure the grid behaves correctly.
3. Observe the GridWorld GUI to confirm actors are placed in the 2D array-based grid.
